    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: 'Narcissus was the most beautiful. He rejected advances of all whom
        admired, so one asked him to be cursed. So he was, cursed to fall in love
        with him own reflection in a pool of water. He perished in agoning and longing,
        turning into the Daffodil. '
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
